Product Description

Revolutionize meal prep with the all-in-one Mueller Pro-Series II, Ultimate Chopper, Mandoline Slicer & Spiralizer!

With its 12-blade options, the Pro Series II will cut your meal preparation time in half and make cooking in the kitchen enjoyable again! Whether you are a busy parent, retired, or just tired of chopping and dicing, the Choppers three different-sized chopper blades, five interchangeable blades for slicing, julienne, grating & shredding, and extra spiralizer offer the functionality of multiple kitchen tools in one unique device. If you dont believe us, give it a try.

CHOPPER

With this Ultimate Chopper, you can choose between 3 blade sizes to dice onions, tomatoes, peppers, potatoes, eggs, garlic, chili and more! In seconds have everything prepped and ready to make your favorite salad, salsa, stir fry or guacamole!

MANDOLINE SLICER

Do you love the perfect slice? Well, the Mueller Ultimate Slicer lets you choose between 2 different blades to give you that unified slice every time! Garnish your dishes, create thin cucumber slices and onion rings or the ultimate potato chip.

GRATER

No more cuts and grazes when grating your cheese, carrots, potatoes and other fruit and vegetables with the 3 blade options. Use the Mueller Safety Food Holder to grate down your ingredients to the last knob. Everything is collected directly into the slide-out Food Container to make things even easier.

Why is Mueller's Pro Series II Vegetable Chopper a cut above the rest?

Healthy and Safe

These kitchen gadgets will alleviate your prep time to just a couple of minutes. Manufactured with top-notch materials like stainless steel blades and non-toxic, food-grade material, Mueller has your health in mind. Your fingers will appreciate it as well no more cuts and no more tears!

Easy to Set Up

Have the device assembled and ready in no time simply replace the blades and lock them in place or rotate the blades when using the spiralizer. This Chopper and Spiralizer combo will save you both time and space, so you wont miss out on any family time!

Easy to Clean & Store

Both the Chopper and the Spiralizer can be disassembled for easy cleaning. Use the handy Cleaning Fork for those hard-to-reach areas before popping all the parts in the top rack of the dishwasher. When clean, the Blades, Food Holder and Spiralizer all neatly pack together for compact storage so no more missing parts!

How customer reviews and ratings work

Customer Reviews, including Product Star Ratings help customers to learn more about the product and decide whether it is the right product for them.

To calculate the overall star rating and percentage breakdown by star, we dont use a simple average. Instead, our system considers things like how recent a review is and if the reviewer bought the item on Amazon. It also analyzed reviews to verify trustworthiness.

    4.0 out of 5 stars Lots of Uses! Super Easy to Use
    Reviewed in the United States on January 1, 2025
    Size: 8 BladeColor: White Sand/GreenVerified Purchase
    The media could not be loaded.
    I already have a non electric chopper device. I have had for quite some time. I would say at least five years if not longer. It has worked and continues to work. My only concern is, I think it might be getting a little old and I definitely wanted to have something on hand before it broke. This is something I use several times a week. And it is a must have for making salsa. The items I use this for most, are chopping up onions and celery and garlic, which is used a lot in my day to day cooking. So what I do is, I saut several skillets full of either just onions or onions and garlic or onions, garlic, and celery. I then freeze them in small containers, noting exactly whats in there. That way when it comes time for dinner prep I always have this already done and I dont have to take the time to saut in a separate skillet. Such a time saver, especially with the very sharp blades. Only one chop is needed to cut through.

    I looked at several devices before settling on this one. So far my husband has mainly been the one to use it. We found it works great on celery and onions. We havent yet used it on potatoes or carrots although we will probably be doing that very soon. I would say the only downside is this, while they do provide a container to store the different blades, there are still multiple other pieces that are a part of this that do not fit. Just the feel of this and handling it tells me its going to last a long time because it is very durable. Definitely well-made.

    We solved that issue by using a black plastic utility container, as pictured, which accommodates all of it very easily. I like keeping everything in one place.

    Therefore, thought for the manufacturer, is to perhaps design something that would hold all the parts and components together.

    There were so many of these to look at and select from on Amazon. However, I really feel this was the best one; very easy to wash up and quickly clean. Im very happy to have it and would definitely recommend it.
